
REACT REDUX TOOLKIT

Terms--> Action, Reducer,Slice,Store


1.  Action: Like an object that describes what happened :object which have an event and information 
    Action → { type: "event", payload: information }
    type → event name EX : Count : inc, dec
    payload → data related to event 

2. Reducer: A function that decides how state changes based on an action.
  (state, action) => newState
  takes current state
  takes action , action " inc" count=+payload , "dec" count-=payload
  returns updated state

3. Slice: A combination of state + reducers + actions in one place.
    Contains:                           counter : counterSlice , products: 
        initial state
        reducer functions
        auto-generated actions

  Purpose:To manage one part of the global state

4. Store: The store is the central place where all application state is stored.
  Store = global container of all state
  To holds the complete state of the app
  To connects all slices
  To allows dispatching actions
  To notifies UI when state changes


One-Line Summary: 
  Action → what happened
  Reducer → how state changes
  Slice → state + logic
  Store → where everything lives


Working: onClick--> handleClick(event)---> Action Dispatch ---> store have Reducer and data(state) information --->Reducer Executes Logic --->State Update in Store --->UI Update  
        user interaction --> your function runs --> sends event to Redux --> decides how to update state --> new state is saved --> React updates automatically


