Async Thunk: In Redux Toolkit createAsyncThunk is used to handle async operations (like API calls)

Real apps need:
            API calls
            delays
            server requests
    That’s where async thunk comes in.

An async thunk automatically creates 3 states:
        pending   → loading
        fulfilled → success
        rejected  → error




